ISLAMABAD, Jul 29 (APP): Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Mohammad Ishaq Dar will lead the Pakistan delegation at the inauguration/oath ceremony of the President-elect of Iran, Dr. Masoud Pezeshkian, to be held on Tuesday (July 30) in Tehran.
The visit attests to the commitment by the two countries to strengthen leadership-level engagement and bilateral cooperation, a statement issued by the Foreign Office said.
